President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to the impact of Hurricane Sandy from October 26 to November 8, 2012. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further damage assessments may result in additional designations. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.